{"bgColorIndex":0,"textColorIndex":1,"note":"<div style=\"background-color: #242b32; padding: 25px; color: #eee8ee; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 25px;\">\n    <h2>Module 1: The Science of Reading &amp; Writing<\/h2>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: 25px;\">\n    <h2 style=\"color: #000000; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><strong>Overview<\/strong><\/h2>\n    <p>Welcome to <em>Module 1: The Science of Reading &amp; Writing. <\/em>This week, we will explore the foundational theories of reading and writing development. You will learn how these theories inform instructional practices and understand the principles of explicit instruction. By the end of this module, you will have a solid grounding in the science behind reading and writing education, which will guide your teaching strategies and interventions.<\/p>\n    <p><img id=\"70647468\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70647468\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"33\" height=\"33\" data-inst-icon-maker-icon=\"true\" data-download-url=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/files\/70647468\/download?download_frd=1&amp;icon_maker_icon=1\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70647468\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/> Begin by completing the <a title=\"Onboarding: Academic Integrity Agreement \" href=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/discussion_topics\/8131198\" data-course-type=\"discussions\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/1616167\/discussion_topics\/8131198\" data-api-returntype=\"Discussion\">Academic Integrity Agreement<\/a> and briefly <a title=\"Course Introduction\" href=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/discussion_topics\/8131193\" data-course-type=\"discussions\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/1616167\/discussion_topics\/8131193\" data-api-returntype=\"Discussion\">introduce (or re-introduce) yourself <\/a>to your peers and to your instructor.&nbsp;<\/p>\n    <p><em>Need Support? Post a question to the<span>&nbsp;<\/span><a title=\"Course Q&amp;A\" href=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/discussion_topics\/8131197\" data-course-type=\"discussions\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/1616167\/discussion_topics\/8131197\" data-api-returntype=\"Discussion\">Course Q&amp;A Discussion Board<\/a>.<\/em><\/p>\n    <hr \/><em>As you read through the Module, please remember to make on-time submissions. <strong>The estimated module completion time is one week, approximately 4 - 4.5 hours.<\/strong><\/em>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"background-color: #ffffff; padding: 25px;\">\n    <h2 style=\"color: #000000; margin-bottom: 20px;\">Learning Outcomes<\/h2>\n    <p>Through active participation in this week's activities, you will:<\/p>\n    <ol>\n        <li>Define reading &amp; writing development and theories.<\/li>\n        <li>Describe how scientific theories inform reading instruction.<\/li>\n        <li>Explain how Ehri's phases of learning to read inform reading development and instruction for typical learners and students with reading difficulties\/disabilities.<\/li>\n        <li>Discuss the principles of explicit instruction.<\/li>\n    <\/ol>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: 25px;\">\n    <h2 style=\"color: #000000; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><strong>Video\/Audio Lecture<\/strong><\/h2>\n    <details style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">\n        <summary style=\"cursor: pointer; font-size: 18px; color: #000000;\">Professor's Video Mini-Lecture<\/summary>\n        <div style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n            <p>This video provides an overview of reading and writing. Topics covered include the five components of Reading, an Overview of Neurodevelopmental Disorders, an Overview of Reading Assessment, Reading Development Theories, and a Simple view of Writing.&nbsp;<\/p>\n            <p style=\"text-align: center;\">&lt;video here&gt;<\/p>\n            <p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<\/p>\n        <\/div>\n    <\/details>\n    <details style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">\n        <summary style=\"cursor: pointer; font-size: 18px; color: #000000;\">Video - Why intensive intervention in reading is important<\/summary>\n        <div style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n            <p>This video describes why intensive intervention in reading is important. Two student case examples are used throughout [26:05 minutes]<\/p>\n            <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe class=\"lti-embed\" style=\"width: 720px; height: 420px;\" title=\"Introduction to Intensive Interventions in Reading\" src=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/external_tools\/retrieve?display=borderless&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fseattleu.instructuremedia.com%2Flti%2Flaunch%3Fcustom_arc_launch_type%3Dbare_embed%26custom_arc_media_id%3D94be9383-c50f-402d-9115-262d04e69eea-121646\" width=\"720\" height=\"420\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"webkitallowfullscreen\" mozallowfullscreen=\"mozallowfullscreen\" allow=\"geolocation *; microphone *; camera *; midi *; encrypted-media *; autoplay *; clipboard-write *; display-capture *\"><\/iframe><\/p>\n        <\/div>\n    <\/details>\n    <details>\n        <summary style=\"cursor: pointer; font-size: 18px; color: #000000;\">Video - Data-based individualization (DBI) in reading<\/summary>\n        <div style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n            <p>This video focuses on how DBI applies to reading. It uses teacher video examples and workbook activities throughout. [1:10:15 minutes]<\/p>\n            <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe class=\"lti-embed\" style=\"width: 720px; height: 420px;\" title=\"Data-based individualization (DBI) in reading\" src=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/external_tools\/retrieve?display=borderless&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fseattleu.instructuremedia.com%2Flti%2Flaunch%3Fcustom_arc_launch_type%3Dbare_embed%26custom_arc_media_id%3D53dc7dc4-1458-44f8-91b6-387b7977a753-121648\" width=\"720\" height=\"420\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"webkitallowfullscreen\" mozallowfullscreen=\"mozallowfullscreen\" allow=\"geolocation *; microphone *; camera *; midi *; encrypted-media *; autoplay *; clipboard-write *; display-capture *\"><\/iframe><\/p>\n        <\/div>\n    <\/details>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"background-color: #ffffff; padding: 25px;\">\n    <h2 style=\"color: #000000; margin-bottom: 20px;\">This Week's Materials<\/h2>\n    <details style=\"border: 1px solid #C3C3C3; margin: 0 0 10px 0; background-color: #ffffff;\">\n        <summary style=\"padding: 10px; cursor: pointer;\">Readings<\/summary>\n        <div style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\">\n            <p><strong>Required Readings<\/strong><\/p>\n            <ul>\n                <li><strong>Teaching Reading Sourcebook<\/strong>:\n                    <ul>\n                        <li><strong>Preface<\/strong>: The Big Picture<\/li>\n                        <li><strong>Chapter 1<\/strong>: The Structure of English<\/li>\n                        <li><strong>Chapter 2<\/strong>: Structure of Spanish<\/li>\n                    <\/ul>\n                <\/li>\n                <li>\n                    <p><a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/jan.ucc.nau.edu\/~jar\/Reading_Wars.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">The Great Debate: Reading Wars<\/a> (by Dr. John Reyhner)<\/p>\n                <\/li>\n                <li>\n                    <p>Baker, S.K., et al. (2017). Learning to read: <a href=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70628286?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70628286\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">\"The simple view of reading.\"<\/a><\/p>\n                <\/li>\n                <li>\n                    <p>Van Dyke, J. A., &amp; Shankweiler, D. P. (2012). <a href=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70628287?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70628287\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">From verbal efficiency theory to lexical quality.<\/a><\/p>\n                <\/li>\n                <li>\n                    <p>Riccomini, P. J., et al. (2017). <a href=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70628285?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70628285\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">Big ideas in special education: Specially designed instruction.<\/a><\/p>\n                <\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n            <p><strong>Optional Readings<\/strong><\/p>\n            <ul>\n                <li>\n                    <p>Moreau, D., &amp; Waldie, K. E. (2016). <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\/pmc\/articles\/PMC4709759\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Developmental Learning Disorders: From Generic Interventions to Individualized Remediation.<\/a><\/p>\n                <\/li>\n                <li>\n                    <p>Torgesen, J. K. (2002). The prevention of reading difficulties. <a href=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70628278?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70628278\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">Journal of School Psychology.<\/a><\/p>\n                <\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n        <\/div>\n    <\/details>\n    <details style=\"border: 1px solid #C3C3C3; margin: 0 0 10px 0; background-color: #ffffff;\">\n        <summary style=\"padding: 10px; cursor: pointer;\">Multimedia\/Resources<\/summary>\n        <div style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\">\n            <ul>\n                <li>\n                    <p><a href=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/media_objects_iframe\/m-287ymHQB1FD6HwRqPeWegChjvMYXyymK?type=video\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Tier II Reading Intervention<\/a><\/p>\n                <\/li>\n                <li>\n                    <p><a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/youtu.be\/gXp1jbFlsfE\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Five Components of Reading<\/a><\/p>\n                <\/li>\n                <li>Teaching Fundamental Reading Skills\n                    <ul>\n                        <li><a href=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/media_objects_iframe\/m-2YRTcVGY6iB2fRr8jAb5fRgfWNdhFjFw?type=video\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Decoding Instruction<\/a> 1st Grade<\/li>\n                        <li><a href=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/media_objects_iframe\/m-648hgCc6cXqaXQXbG4p3JapaCDkTiuz2?type=video\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Vocabulary Instruction<\/a> 2nd Grade<\/li>\n                        <li><a href=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/media_objects_iframe\/m-5ke42eZguV17Vn8VKgbYUcmQkYz97ZVX?type=video\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cause &amp; Effect<\/a> 3rd Grade<\/li>\n                    <\/ul>\n                <\/li>\n                <li>\n                    <p><a href=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70628284?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70628284\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">Downloadable Explicit Instruction Graphic Organizer<\/a><\/p>\n                <\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n        <\/div>\n    <\/details>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: 25px;\">\n    <h2 style=\"color: #000000; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><strong>Your Tasks to Complete &amp; Submit<\/strong><\/h2>\n    <p><em><strong>Directions<\/strong>: Select <strong>ONE Theory Assignment <\/strong>from Part 1 and <strong>ONE Practice Assignment<\/strong> from Part 2 to demonstrate your understanding of this week's content. Post your response to the discussion board linked below.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n    <h3>Part 1 - Theory<\/h3>\n    <details style=\"border: 1px solid #C3C3C3; margin: 0 0 10px 40px; background-color: #ffffff;\">\n        <summary style=\"padding: 10px;\">Theory Assignment A<\/summary>\n        <p style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\"><strong>Case Study: Applying Reading and Writing Development Theories in a School Psychology Context<\/strong><\/p>\n        <p style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\">Sophia is a second-grade student who has been referred to you, the school psychologist, due to her struggles with both reading and writing. Your assessment reveals that Sophia has difficulty decoding words, reads slowly, and often fails to comprehend the main ideas of passages. In writing, Sophia struggles to generate ideas, organize her thoughts, and produce coherent sentences and paragraphs.<\/p>\n        <p style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\">As the school psychologist, you are tasked with developing an intervention plan that addresses Sophia's challenges in both reading and writing. Using your knowledge of reading and writing development theories and evidence-based practices in school psychology, create a multi-step plan that applies these theories to support Sophia's growth.<\/p>\n        <p style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\">In your 4 - 5 paragraph response:<\/p>\n        <ol style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">\n            <li>Identify one reading development theory and one writing development theory that are most relevant to Sophia's case. Consider theories that are commonly used in the field of school psychology.<\/li>\n            <li>Create an outline of an intervention plan that applies the key principles of a chosen theory to address Sophia's needs. Include at least one specific strategy or activity for reading or writing that is evidence-based and commonly used by school psychologists.&nbsp;\n                <div class=\"border-round-t\" style=\"background-color: #c0392b; padding: 10px; margin: 0px;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;\">Intervention Plan Outline<\/span><\/div>\n                <div class=\"border-round-b\" style=\"border: 1px solid #c0392b; padding: 5px 15px 1px 15px;\">\n                    <p><strong>Intervention Plan<\/strong><\/p>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li><strong>Reading Intervention<\/strong>:<\/li>\n                    <\/ul>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Phonemic Awareness and Phonics Instruction<\/li>\n                    <\/ul>\n                    <ul>\n                        <ul>\n                            <ul>\n                                <li>Activities:<\/li>\n                            <\/ul>\n                        <\/ul>\n                    <\/ul>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Guided Oral Reading Practices<\/li>\n                    <\/ul>\n                    <ul>\n                        <ul>\n                            <ul>\n                                <li>Activities:<\/li>\n                            <\/ul>\n                        <\/ul>\n                    <\/ul>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li><strong>Writing Intervention<\/strong>:<\/li>\n                    <\/ul>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Brainstorming and Graphic Organizers<\/li>\n                    <\/ul>\n                    <ul>\n                        <ul>\n                            <ul>\n                                <li>Activities:<\/li>\n                            <\/ul>\n                        <\/ul>\n                    <\/ul>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Structured Writing Frames<\/li>\n                    <\/ul>\n                    <ul>\n                        <ul>\n                            <ul>\n                                <li>Activities:<\/li>\n                            <\/ul>\n                        <\/ul>\n                    <\/ul>\n                <\/div>\n            <\/li>\n            <li>Discuss how you would collaborate with Sophia's teachers and parents to implement the intervention plan and monitor her progress. Explain how you would use data-based decision-making to adjust your interventions based on Sophia's response.<\/li>\n            <li>Consider the role of a school psychologist in supporting students with reading and writing difficulties. Reflect on how this case study informs your understanding of school psychologists' unique contributions to addressing literacy challenges.<\/li>\n        <\/ol>\n    <\/details>\n    <details style=\"border: 1px solid #C3C3C3; margin: 0 0 10px 40px; background-color: #ffffff;\">\n        <summary style=\"padding: 10px;\">Theory Assignment B<\/summary>\n        <p style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\">Using the Simple View of Reading (SVR) theory, in 4 - 5 paragraphs, explain how deficits in decoding and linguistic comprehension skills can lead to reading difficulties. Provide an example of how a student with weaknesses in each area might present in the classroom and describe targeted interventions that address each skill deficit.<\/p>\n    <\/details>\n    <h3>Part 2 - Practice<\/h3>\n    <details style=\"border: 1px solid #C3C3C3; margin: 0 0 10px 40px; background-color: #ffffff;\">\n        <summary style=\"padding: 10px;\">Practice Assignment A<\/summary>\n        <div style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\">\n            <ol>\n                <li>Read the article \"Big ideas in special education: Specially designed instruction, high-leverage practices, explicit instruction, and intensive instruction\" by Riccomini, Morano, &amp; Hughes (2017).<\/li>\n                <li>Create a visual representation (e.g., infographic, mind map, or graphic organizer) that summarizes the key components of explicit instruction and how they support student learning.<\/li>\n                <li>In the same written reflection, discuss how understanding explicit instruction principles can help you design more effective interventions for students with reading and writing difficulties. Share your visual representation and reflection on the discussion board.<\/li>\n            <\/ol>\n        <\/div>\n    <\/details>\n    <details style=\"border: 1px solid #C3C3C3; margin: 0 0 10px 40px; background-color: #ffffff;\">\n        <summary style=\"padding: 10px;\">Practice Assignment B<\/summary>\n        <div style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\">\n            <ol>\n                <li>Watch the video \"<span>Why intensive intervention in reading is important<\/span>\" and study the cases presented.<\/li>\n                <li>Select one of the case studies and develop a brief intervention plan incorporating data-based individualization (DBI) principles and intensive intervention. Your plan should include:\n                    <ol>\n                        <li>Identification of the student's specific reading difficulties<\/li>\n                        <li>Selection of an evidence-based intervention that targets the identified skill deficits<\/li>\n                        <li>A plan for progress monitoring and data collection<\/li>\n                        <li>Criteria for making data-based decisions about the effectiveness of the intervention<\/li>\n                    <\/ol>\n                <\/li>\n                <li>Share your intervention plan on the discussion board and provide constructive feedback on at least one of your peers' plans. In your feedback, consider the alignment of the intervention with the student's needs, the appropriateness of the progress monitoring plan, and the clarity of the decision-making criteria.<\/li>\n            <\/ol>\n        <\/div>\n    <\/details>\n<\/div>\n<p><strong><img role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70647468\/download\" alt=\"\" width=\"33\" height=\"33\" data-inst-icon-maker-icon=\"true\" data-download-url=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/files\/70647468\/download?download_frd=1&amp;icon_maker_icon=1\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70647468\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/> Submit your responses <a href=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/discussion_topics\/8131192?wrap=1\">Module 1 Discussion Board<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n<div style=\"border-left: 4px solid #C3C3C3; padding: 25px; margin: 20px 0; background-color: #ffffff;\">\n    <h4 style=\"color: #000000; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><strong><img id=\"70647454\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70647454\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"33\" height=\"33\" data-inst-icon-maker-icon=\"true\" data-download-url=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/files\/70647454\/download?download_frd=1&amp;icon_maker_icon=1\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70647454\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/> Peer Response Requirement<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p><span>Read\/view your peer's submission and respond to at least&nbsp;<\/span><strong>ONE<\/strong><span>&nbsp;of your peers in about a paragraph or more.<\/span><\/p>\n    <details>\n        <summary style=\"cursor: pointer; font-size: 18px; color: #000000; margin-top: 10px;\">Peer Response Sentence Starters and Engagement Questions<\/summary>\n        <div style=\"padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;\">\n            <p>Use these sentence starters and questions to help you respond to your peers:<\/p>\n            <ul>\n                <li>I found your response interesting because...<\/li>\n                <li>I agree with your point about... because...<\/li>\n                <li>I respectfully disagree with your statement about... because...<\/li>\n                <li>Your response made me think about... in a new way.<\/li>\n                <li>Can you clarify what you meant by...?<\/li>\n                <li>How do you think... relates to the concepts we learned in this module?<\/li>\n                <li>What new insights or perspectives did you gain from reading your peer's response?<\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n        <\/div>\n    <\/details>\n<\/div>\n<hr \/>\n<div style=\"background-color: #ffffff; padding: 25px;\">\n    <h2 style=\"color: #000000; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><strong><img id=\"70628269\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70628269\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"59\" height=\"59\" data-inst-icon-maker-icon=\"true\" data-download-url=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/files\/70628269\/download?download_frd=1&amp;icon_maker_icon=1\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/seattleu.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/1616167\/files\/70628269\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/> This Week's Task Schedule<\/strong><\/h2>\n    <ul>\n        <li><strong>Tuesday:<\/strong> Complete the Academic Integrity requirement, Introduction, and required material<\/li>\n        <li><strong>Wednesday:<\/strong> Please post your initial submission by the end of the day<\/li>\n        <li><strong>Thursday - Sunday:<\/strong> Read and respond to at least ONE of your peer's posts<\/li>\n    <\/ul>\n    <p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Click on the <strong>Next<\/strong>&nbsp;button below to continue in this module.<\/em>&nbsp;▼<\/p>"}